She has already been through IVF twice, giving birth to two sets of twins. One of her twins died suddenly when he failed to wake up from a nap one Christmas, and she decided that, at the age of 43, she wanted to have more child­ren, but she couldn’t face going through the gruelling medication required for IVF again. Like other evangelicals she had opted not to cryopreserve her own embryos during the previous rounds of IVF. ‘I didn’t want my people in a freezer,’ she says. ‘The thawing process is just very dangerous – but we loved the idea of these other couples realising that they were child­ren they had frozen, and placing them for adoption.’ She feels inspired to rescue embryos. ‘Some people go to this because they can’t conceive but we have heard really great teaching and preaching on rescuing these embryos.
